Lifebank founder, Temie Giwa-Tubosun, in her interview with AllAfrica's Juanita Williams and Sethi Ncube spoke about her passion for building a better world for women, especially pregnant women, from her experience working with the World Health Organisation, and then the final spark of the difficult delivery of her son, which inspired her to start Lifebank. Founded in 2016, Lifebank is a healthcare technology and logistics startup, based in Lagos, Nigeria. The company facilitates the transmission of blood from labs across the country to patients and doctors in hospitals. Read on. Visit Prosper Africa to access U.S. Government trade and investment support and browse the Virtual Deal Room with curated investment opportunities, including companies life LifeBank. Visit Prosper Africa Women Innovators Special Section on AllAfrica.